listing.name: Excel + Trello 2-Way Sync
listing.description:
Sync Trello cards with Excel rows using this powerful integration.

---

## Sync information from Trello into Excel and get real-time insights on project performance
With Unito, sync Trello cards to rows in Excel and keep everything updated automatically. Build powerful reports in Excel to get insights on progress in Trello with no manual work.

Unito also supports 2-way workflows, which means changes made in Excel are synced back to your Trello cards. You can also use Unito to automatically create new Trello cards when a new row is created in Excel. Unito helps keep everything in perfect sync across any workflow that needs Excel and Trello.

![Trello - Excel Integration](https://unito.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/TrelloExcel.mp4.gif)

## Features
### Supports essential Trello fields
Unito has some of the deepest two-way integrations for Trello. Sync card names, due dates, assignees, card status, card descriptions, labels, list names, board names, and more. You can manually map these fields with any Excel column and keep your data in sync.

### Customize in real-time
Unito integrations allow data to flow across tools in real-time. Customize your flow to your exact needs and set powerful filters to define what you need synced. Make changes to your flow and they’ll be reflected in your tools in real-time.

### No-code and self-serve
Unito requires no coding knowledge. Any team can integrate Trello with Excel and build the workflow they need in a few clicks.

### Step-by-step walkthrough
Need more help? Follow our detailed guide on how to [sync Trello cards with Microsoft Excel](https://unito.io/blog/guide-how-to-sync-trello-cards-with-microsoft-excel/?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=trello_excel).

## What Unito customers are saying
* Excellent! [...] It’s a great product and the perfect solution for our needs. It was exactly what we needed to pull information together into one place.
* [...] It’s like someone flipped on the light switch. Now communication, tasks, and status flow seamlessly across boards, teams, and org structures.
* I’m able to sync the issues I want from Jira to my Trello board, without having to play around in the developers’ board. They have their workflow, I have mine. All the info I need is synced continuously. [...]


## FAQ
### Does Unito also work with other tools?
Absolutely! You can sync Trello with Asana, Jira, Wrike, GitHub, GitLab, Airtable, ClickUp, Azure DevOps, HubSpot, Salesforce, Notion, [and many more tools](https://unito.io/connectors/?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=trello_excel)!

### Is Unito a free Power-Up?
Unito is free to try for 14 days, no credit card required. After that, you'll need to subscribe to one of our paid plans.

### I'm having an issue, where can I turn to?
Our [Help Center](https://guide.unito.io/unitos-trello-power-ups/en/?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=trello_excel) has troubleshooting guides for common Unito issues, information on all our integrations, and more!

### Does Unito support custom fields?
We do! You can sync custom fields with Unito during your free trial. After that, you'll need to subscribe to one of our paid plans.

---

## Get started for free now!
Directly access and start using Unito through this power-up, or head to Unito to learn more about our [Trello Excel integration](https://unito.io/integrations/trello-microsoft-excel/?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=trello_excel) and start your free trial. Find more detailed information about Unito's Trello Excel integration in Unito's [Help Center](https://guide.unito.io/microsoft-excel-integration/?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=trello_excel).

listing.name: Timeflow Tracker
listing.description:
## **Timeflow Tracker**: Optimize Your Trello Workflow with Precision
**Timeflow Tracker** is a dynamic plugin for Trello, meticulously crafted to elevate project management to new heights. This tool is not just an add-on; it's a game-changer for teams seeking to maximize efficiency in their workflow. By integrating seamlessly with your Trello boards, Timeflow Tracker offers real-time, actionable insights into card transitions, transforming how you manage projects.

**Why Timeflow Tracker?**
 - **Clarity in Workflow:** Understand at a glance how time is allocated across various stages of your project.
 - **Identify Bottlenecks:** Instantly spot areas needing improvement, ensuring smoother project progression.
 - **Data-Driven Decisions:** Make informed choices based on comprehensive time tracking data.


**Key Features:**
 - **Time Tracking Per Card:** Witness the journey of each card, tracking its time across columns.
 - **Instant Reports:** A click away, generate detailed reports for an in-depth analysis of workflow patterns.
 - **Selective Column Analysis:** Tailor your tracking by selecting specific columns, focusing on critical transitions.
 - **Average Card Time:** Benchmark your efficiency with average transit times for cards.
 - **Comprehensive Card List:** Dive deep into your project with a list detailing card names and transition times.


**How It Works:**
 - **Easy Installation:** Add Timeflow Tracker from the Trello Power-Ups directory.
 - **Simple Authentication:** A one-time, straightforward step to link the plugin with your Trello data.
 - **Customizable Tracking:** Choose columns for detailed analysis using intuitive dropdowns.
 - **Real-Time Insights:** Watch as the plugin accurately records card movements.
 - **Actionable Reports:** Generate insights at the click of a button, driving efficiency and productivity.


Visual Walkthrough:
![See Timeflow Tracker in Action](https://timeflow-powerup.on.dev-craft.tech/trello-plugin.gif)

GIF: Experience how Timeflow Tracker seamlessly integrates with your Trello boards, offering a visual and intuitive user interface.

**Elevate Your Trello Experience:**
Timeflow Tracker is more than a plugin; it's your partner in project management. By offering a clear window into how your team works, it empowers you to make impactful changes, streamline processes, and ultimately, achieve your project goals with greater efficiency and less effort.

*Ready to transform your Trello workflow? Install Timeflow Tracker today and experience the difference!*

- Exportieren Sie den Kalender eines Boards an Kalender von Drittanbietern mithilfe des eindeutigen iCalendar-Links eines Boards.

## What is it about?
Statuses & Workflow provides an ultimate solution for Statuses and Workflow management: it makes your process intuitive and easy to follow – this is exactly what you’ve been waiting for! Not only does it maintain the Workflow of your Trello board, but it can do handy *automation* for you, like moving a card to a specific list, managing card members, setting due date, completing checklists, and doing whatever you want with joy. The best part is that the product has been in active development all this time, and we still have a lot of features to implement, stay tuned! 😉

![How does it work?](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/how-it-works.gif)

🧡 Statuses & Workflow is designed and developed by ThunderModules – fastest growing new publisher of 2022 🧡

## Enhance your workflow with our solutions!
Try [Card Done](https://trello.com/power-ups/6244a5a256399f22036820cb) to complete your Trello cards in just one click ✅
Try [Tables & Spreadsheets](https://trello.com/power-ups/65c7808c749e34145008f9b4) to create tables directly within your Trello cards 🦖

---

# Statuses 💥
Yep, that’s exactly what you are thinking of – the tool to keep your workflow’s statuses up to date, organized, and transparent!

![Status creation](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/status-creation.webp)

Create, update, and drag & drop your Statuses, set up unique to your team flow with special colors and icons. We also support Status enabling|disabling and the ability to hide a Status from a card’s front side. Statuses are not related to Trello lists and do not depend on them (you can keep cards with a variety of statuses in one Trello list).

![Status settings](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/status-settings.png)

**Default List** – сhange statuses with just a swipe! Yeah, as easy as it sounds!
The default list can be set from the status settings – select any list in a board you want. Then, any card that appears in that list will have status and actions applied to it.

**Easy Switch** – we understand that working with complicated processes is not easy. That's why we introduce a painkiller – Easy Switch!
Select as many statuses as you want to be listed as Card Buttons so that you can switch to that statuses right from a card view by simply pressing a Button. You are welcome to specify a unique set of easy-switch statuses for each status.

**Description** – want to leave a note for teammates? – Description is the tool! 
It's visible in a status header on the Statuses page and improves onboarding with your custom notes about status usage. Members can hover over a description to get into the process.

# Actions 🤖
Automation that is triggered on a card when you select a status – we call it Action. We prepared a lot of them!

![Dates-members-labels](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/actions-dates-members-labels.png)

### Dates Actions 🗓
Always wanted to keep your team accountable for timelines? Add due dates to cards based on Status.

Due date automation (on Status selection):
- Set due date to now;
- Set due date on a specific date or in a particular timeline;
- Ask member to select due date on Status selection;
- Remove due date;
- Mark due date as (in)complete.

### Members Actions 👥
Assign work on specific members based on a card Status!

Members automation (on Status selection):
- Remove|add all members from|to a card;
- Remove|add status changer from|to a card;
- Remove|add particular members from|to a card;

### Labels Actions 🏷
Nearly-native way to keep the right labels assigned to the right cards! You can select to remove all labels from a card or to add a specific set of labels. Either way, we keep labels up to date with your board settings so no need to update labels in the power-up settings.

### Checklists and Other Actions ✅
![Move-comment-checklists](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/actions-move-comment-checklists.png)

Automating checklists can be annoying, that’s why we put additional effort to make them easy to setup and use.

Checklists automation (on Status selection):
- Add a new checklist with checklists to a card;
- Complete a checklist in a card, also you can select to complete all checklists in a card;
- Remove a checklist in a card, remove all checklists in a card;
More to come!

### Other Actions
Smaller, but still useful actions:

- **Comment** – designed to automatically leave a comment in a card, you can also ask member to leave a comment during status selection;
- **Move** – it moves a card to a selected list in your workspace (any public board);
- **Remove** – allows you to archive or delete a card on status selection;

# Analytics 📊
What's an average time per status? Which statuses are used most frequently? Do you want to dive deeper into the data?

Four amazing charts to help you in the investigation!
![Analytics demo](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/analytics.png)

**Statuses Now Chart** – сards with statuses currently on your board. It’s as simple as that! Helps to understand the current state of a board and the cards in it. You can filter that chart by status to hide some of them.

**Timeline Chart** is designed to show the average time per status and identify potential blockers in your process. Use it to make your workflow smoother! BTW, you can filter that chart by a time range to see how the timeline has changed over time.

**Usage Chart** – want to know which statuses are used most frequently? Statuses Usage is the tool for you! Check how many statuses have been applied, which ones, and when. Maybe it’s time to groom rarely-used statuses or even let them go.

**Transitions Chart** – if you want to investigate a status or learn more about its’ transitions, try the Transitions chart! Simply select a status to analyze and view all the transitions In and Out!

We are excited to continue working on Statuses & Workflow power up and here is **the plan**:

![Roadmap](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/roadmap.png)

**We will add new features as soon as they are tested and ready to go**. Also, the priority of features depends on your feedback. In this way, we can learn from you, analyze your interest in the Statuses & Workflow power-up, and grow wisely with excellent quality!

If you want to help us deliver faster, please share the power-up with your fellows!
